Here is an example of a code for path traversal in PHP:

```
<?php

$path = '/var/www/html';
$dir = scandir($path);

foreach ($dir as $file) {
    if ($file == '..' || $file == '.') {
        continue;
    }
    echo $file. "\n";
    $path = $path. '/'. $file;
    echo scandir($path). "\n";
}

?>
```

This code first sets the `$path` variable to the directory that we want to traverse. We then use the `scandir()` function to get an array of all the files and directories in that directory. We then loop through this array using a `foreach` loop and check if the current file is `..` or `.` (which represent the parent directory and the current directory respectively). If it is, we skip over that file using the `continue` statement.

Otherwise, we print out the name of the file and then set the `$path` variable to the new directory by appending the name of the file to the `$path` variable. We then call `scandir()` again on the new directory and print out the results.

This process continues until we reach the root directory (`/`).

def create_children():
    while True:
        try:
            pid = os.fork()
            if pid > 0:
                # parent process
                print("Child process created:", pid)
                create_children()
            elif pid == 0:
                # child process
                print("Child process created:", pid)
                os._exit(0)
        except OSError:
            # fork failed
            print("fork failed")
            break

